================================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================================

Reverie's DynamoRIO-based dynamic binary instrumentation backend (reverie-dbi)
depends on DynamoRIO. DynamoRIO is referenced as a git submodule at
`third-party/dynamorio` and is configured, built, and installed on demand by
`reverie-dbi/build.rs`. No DynamoRIO source or binaries are redistributed in
this repository; only the submodule commit reference is stored here.

Building reverie-dbi therefore fetches and builds DynamoRIO and, transitively,
the third-party projects that DynamoRIO itself vendors as submodules. The
licenses of those components are summarized below. This NOTICE is provided for
attribution and awareness; the authoritative and complete license texts live in
each upstream project. Anyone who *distributes* binaries produced from this
build must comply with all of the licenses listed here, including the copyleft
(LGPL) obligations noted for elfutils and certain DynamoRIO extensions.

